items.abstract:
Please Note: By registering for this session, it does not guarantee you a seat. Seating is available on a first come first seated basis. This session is an introduction to Golang - the Go programming language - for IT Professionals.
We'll explain how to setup a GO development environment, create a simple HTTP/2 Web API, and embed our code into a Docker container. We'll also go through the reasons why the language is so popular to create network applications by showing how the language is expressive, concise, clean, and efficient. 

Join this session if you've started writing Python scripts that consume Web APIs, and you now want to go to the next stage by creating your own APIs to expose or store Enterprise Data. Takes place in DevNet Zone.

session.title: GoLang 101 for ITPros
DevNet Workshop- From Zero to a Network Application with GoLang

participants.bio:
Stve Sfartz is API Evangelist at Cisco DevNet, spreading the word for Cisco REST APIs and Cisco Spark Cloud Collaboration Services, and helping Developers and Systems Engineers differentiate their product and accelerate their business.
You're a Startup, an Enterprise or an Independent Software Vendor? Feel free to ping Stve to discuss innovation and how to integrate CISCO APIs into your applications.
As a strong supporter of Web APIs, Stve has committed himself to teach developer communities how to consume and build APIs in various languages.
Meet Stve at a DevNet event or during a Hackathon:
